KW  - Federal funds
AB  - This paper finds that risk premiums on overnight interbank loans increase dramatically at year-end. Further, cross-sectional variation in prices reflects, in part, differences in public disclosure requirements across institutions, suggesting a significant influence of window dressing on behavior in this market.
